prerequisities

pip install flask
pip install Flask
pip install xml.dom.minidom
pip install rdflib
pip install nltk


cd into folder Server_files

All three server-side files : init.py, query_run.py and mapper.py should be placed in the same folder.
In the directory where we have our init.py file create a folder called “templates” and place the two html files “main.html” and “success.html” in the folder.


run the following command

> cd Server_files
> python init.py


The following screen is flashed after a certain wait time as .ttl files are loaded (.ttl is extension of semantic triples using which the knowledge graph is stored)

Time taken to load TTL 176.20316982269287
 * Serving Flask app "init" (lazy loading)
 * Environment: production
   WARNING: This is a development server. Do not use it in a production deployment.
   Use a production WSGI server instead.
 * Debug mode: off
 * Running on http://0.0.0.0:5000/ (Press CTRL+C to quit)


 Copy http://0.0.0.0:5000/ and paste in an internet explorer

 Once the query interface is live, try queryimg

 Example queries

 any construct name  (like write_ptr)

 list all variables in a file -----    ( use any file name for the libpng github  project like pngwutil.c)

 how many unsynchronised read and write sequence of variables involved in handler

 constructs related to sorting

 list extern variables and the file where it is defined

 if the query engine crashes (unexpected input, etc.). go back and requery

